      • getTypeName

        public String getTypeName()
        Description copied from interface: JavaTypeDescriptor
        Get the type name. This is useful for dynamic models which either will not have a Java type (JavaTypeDescriptor.getJavaType() returns null) or JavaTypeDescriptor.getJavaType() returns a non-indicative value (java.util.Map.class for a composite value in EntityMode.MAP EntityMode, e.g.).

        For typed models, this generally returns JavaTypeDescriptor.getJavaType().getName

        Specified by:
        getTypeName in interface JavaTypeDescriptor<T>
        Returns:
        The Java type name.
